---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service">
  <section class="min-h-screen pt-32 pb-20 px-4 md:px-16 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-serif text-dark dark:text-cream opacity-0 animate-[fade-up_1s_ease-out_forwards]">
        Terms of <span class="italic text-coral">Service</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl font-sans text-dark/60 dark:text-cream/60 mt-6 opacity-0 animate-[fade-up_1s_ease-out_0.3s_forwards]">
        The ground rules for our lovely interactions on this site. 🤝
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12 font-sans text-lg text-dark/80 dark:text-cream/80 opacity-0 animate-[fade-up_1s_ease-out_0.6s_forwards]">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-dark dark:text-cream mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Welcome to my cozy corner of the internet! By browsing this portfolio, you agree to these simple terms. They are here to make sure everyone plays nice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-dark dark:text-cream mb-4">2. Intellectual Property 🎨</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          All the designs, images, code, and content on this site are my original work unless otherwise stated. Feel free to use them for inspiration, but please don't steal or claim them as your own! If you want to use something, just ask.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-dark dark:text-cream mb-4">3. Working Together</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Reaching out through this website doesn't automatically mean we are in a binding contract. Official projects will be followed up with formal agreements so we're both protected and happy!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-dark dark:text-cream mb-4">4. Updates to Terms</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          I might occasionally update these terms to reflect new features or keep up with the law. Just check back here if you're ever curious. Let's keep making great things!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
